<h2>The NTP Bug Tracking System</h2>
<p>The quickest way to bring bugs and issues to the attention of the NTP
Developers is to use the <a href="http://bugs.ntp.org/">NTP Bug Tracking
System</a>. Reports submitted in this manner will be immediately forwarded to
the NTP Developers.</p>

<h2>bugs@ntp.org</h2>
<p>Bug reports may be sent to <a href="mailto:bugs@ntp.org">bugs@ntp.org</a>.
Please keep in mind that reports submitted in the manner must first be
reviewed (to filter out spam) and then forwarded to the NTP Developers for
consideration. This may entail some delay.</p>
<p>You may be contacted for additional information before your report is
forwarded to the NTP Developers.</p>
<p>You may be asked to register at the <a
href="http://bugs.ntp.org/">NTP Bug Tracking System</a> to facilitate
discussion of the issue you have reported.</p>

